metadata.name: Psilocybin 250 mg #177
metadata.description:
Celebrating 2500 projects on fxhash by releasing 250 unique editions to collect for free.

This generative art project is based on Plate 18 in J. Bourgoin's 1879 seminal work on Arabic geometrical patterns. Implemented in 3471 hand-crafted characters of JS code. London, December 2021.

Trigger warning: some of these artworks produce flashing images and rapidly changing colors which may pose a risk of seizure to people with photosensitive epilepsy or similar conditions.

metadata.name: Modulation #250
metadata.description:
Isometric cityscapes, patterns and geometries generated by trigonometric functions and rendered as SVG.

The SVG can be saved by pressing "s" on the full-screen view.
A PNG version can be exported by pressing "e" on the full-screen view.

By default the dimensions of the export are 6000×7500.
These dimensions can be changed by adding, for example, ?w=12000 to the full-screen page URL, where w is the desired width. Then press "e" to export at this size.

metadata.name: Hexagones Landscape #351
metadata.description:
An undulating (sometimes) landscape made up of hexagons (or "Hexagones" laying in wait) to celebrate the first birthday of fxhash. Written at the last minute the weekend before the birthday week.

A simpler 16 colour version of this project was originally coded on an Atari ST 512, about 32 years ago, figured it was time to update it.

INSTRUCTIONS ::

h - Toggle high-res
s - Download and save image

PRINTING INSTRUCTIONS ::

High-res will output a 6,553 x 8,192 image, at 300dpi it should print at...

21.84 x 27.3 inches
55.47 x 69.3 cm

metadata.name: DisOrder #18
metadata.description:
Manual Dutch Auction (DA): 84 · 56 · 38 · 26 · 18  every 8 minutes.
Auction will stop changing price when non-reserves are fully minted.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////

All that is, starts with Order.

Order attempts to evade entropy by following its own intrinsic patterns. Then, inevitably, there is change: an anomaly, a nudge that turns into a catalyst for widespread change.The momentum cannot be stopped.

Brief cycles build upon themselves, iterating and breaking into something new with each turn. Now, looking back, the accumulation of small divergences look like a leap, with trails of evolutionary decline casting tall shadows on the patterns that bore them.

The beauty of what this entropy creates, rises beyond chaos. It represents the past, and signals the future, and suddenly looks like a wild take on Order itself – the true DisOrder of life.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////

FEATURES :
21 Features implemented including colors, styles, technical parameters...

INTERACTIVITY :
Press ‘h’ in live mode for a list of options.
Press 's' to save an image of the output at the current resolution
Press ‘1’-’9’ to increase resolution
...
